# Sprint 2 cycle-3 fixture (paper §3.2 paged-KV end-to-end wiring).
#
# Pins the decorator-to-codegen wiring: bare `@paged_kv` alongside
# `@flash_attention` must reach `FlashAttentionConfig::paged=true`,
# which (a) appends the `_p1_` variant tag to the synthesized kernel
# name and (b) emits the block-table indirection block in PTX
# (`flash_attention.rs:1622-1649`).
#
# `block_size=32` exercises the @paged_kv arg-parsing path
# (`compiler/kernel.rs:1007-1020`). Note: `block_size` is consumed at
# compile time only for the `block_kv % block_size` alignment check
# (`compiler/kernel.rs:1167`); it is NOT stored on
# `FlashAttentionConfig`, so the integration test cannot pin it
# through the compile context. The runtime kernel parameter
# `.param .u64 block_size` is wired at launch time, not codegen time.
# The single-config codepath defaults to `block_kv=64`, so
# `block_size=32` divides cleanly and the alignment validation passes.
#
# Body is intentionally trivial — the integration test only inspects
# the compile context, the synthesized kernel name, and the PTX byte
# stream, none of which depend on the function body.

@flash_attention
@paged_kv(block_size=32)
fn forward():
    pass
